   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Seventy-five THE PEACE OF THE CROSS Scripture: Col 1:20 The problem in the universe The biggest problem in the universe is disharmony among all the creatures.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Everything in the universe has this problem with God.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The reason the creatures are in disharmony with God is that man is in disharmony with God.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>This is due to man s sin.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>For example, mosquitoes and insects bite, and animals kill each other.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>This is all because man is out of harmony with God, which is the result of man s sin.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>When sin came in, the whole universe became full of chaos.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The peace of the universe The universe is out of harmony because of man s sin.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Therefore, before the universe can have peace, man s sin must be removed.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Man s sin was removed when Christ shed His blood on the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Thus, through the shedding of His blood, Christ made peace in the universe.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The function of the peace of the cross The peace of the cross firstly reconciles man to God.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The peace of the cross also reconciles all things in the universe to God.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>How to obtain the peace of the cross Confess your own sin and your disharmony with God.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Confess that Jesus died on the cross for your sins.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Accept the Lord Jesus to be your Savior and your peace with God.</S>
   </TEXT>
